Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @cauliflower florets{300} into a #mixing bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir in the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Make sure the florets are well coated. In another #small bowl{}, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} with half the @Central American style spice mix{1%tsp}. Season the crumbs with @salt{} and stir in a glug of @oil{}(glug). Tip the crumbs onto the florets and toss to coat evenly.

Carefully transfer the florets to a lined #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. Discard any crumbs that are left in the bowl.

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Transfer a third to a #bowl{} and crush with a #fork{} (we will use these later to thicken the bean stew). Trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways, then chopped widthways into small chunks). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the courgette and cook, stirring for ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and remaining spice mix, cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped) and @water{75%ml}. Bring to a simmer, then leave to bubble away for ~{5%minutes}. After 5 mins, add the whole and crushed beans to the stew. Cook until the stew is nice and thick, ~{5-6%minutes} more.

Do any washing up now whilst everything is cooking. When the cauliflower is ready, remove from the oven. Stir half the coriander into the stew, then remove from the heat. Season the stew with @salt{} and as much red chilli as you like!

Spoon the spicy bean stew into #bowls{} and add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}. Carefully arrange the cauliflower nuggets on top and finish with a sprinkling of remaining coriander. Enjoy!